      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Crop Leaching Requirement Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farm_Crop_Properties_Dialog_Bo" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Land Use Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">CROP_MAX_LEACHING_REQUIREMENT </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The crop leaching requirement is the fraction of total irrigation (applied) water that must pass through the soil to prevent the soil salinity from reaching the tolerance of the crop.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">RHOADES Equation ==&gt; ECw/(5*ECe - ECw)</text></para>
